Prominent Texas lawyer Harry Whittington, accidentally shot by Vice President Dick Cheney while hunting, is in stable condition at a Corpus Christi hospital.
The incident, where Cheney mistook Whittington for a quail, sparked media attention and questions about transparency.
Whittington, a millionaire attorney, suffered pellet wounds to his face, neck, and chest.
Cheney, known for his hunting trips, will receive a warning for not having the required bird hunting stamp.
The delay in reporting the incident raised concerns, with the White House facing scrutiny over the handling of the situation.
